<app xmlns="http://github.com/lindenb/jvarkit/" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" app="&name;" package="&package;" __placeholder__="1">
<description>Lift-over a VCF file</description>
<input type="vcf"/>
<output type="vcf"/>

<options>
	<option name="liftOverFile" type="input-file" opt="f" longopt="chain">
		<description>LiftOver chain file</description>
	</option>
	<option name="failedFile" type="output-file" opt="X" longopt="failed">
		<description>write variants failing the liftOver here</description>
	</option>
	<option name="minMatch" type="double" opt="m" longopt="minMatch" default="0.95">
		<description> lift over min-match</description>
	</option>
	<option name="REF" type="input-file" opt="R" longopt="REF" >
		<description>indexed reference file with the new sequence dictionary. Optional.</description>
	</option>
</options>


<documentation>
<h:h1>Deprecated</h:h1>
Use GATK LiftoverVariants https://www.broadinstitute.org/gatk/gatkdocs/org_broadinstitute_gatk_tools_walkers_variantutils_LiftoverVariants.php


<h:h3>Motivation</h:h3>
[LiftOver](http://genome.ucsc.edu/cgi-bin/hgLiftOver) a VCF file. The program uses the following picard LiftOver class: http://picard.sourceforge.net/javadoc/net/sf/picard/liftover/LiftOver.html

<h:h3>Warning</h:h3>

The **##contig=** lines are not changed if option -D is not used.

The program currently doesn't look at the strand.

